{
  "texts": [
    "Comparing this expression with that for the bias-corrected regression, the latter is more precise if",
    "Unsurprisingly, this comparison depends on the relative size of the validation sample versus the primary sample.",
    "But notice that it further depends on the relative standard deviation of the existing measurement V r and the LLM's error ∆ r.",
    "Importantly, Equation (14) therefore implies that the bias-corrected regression coefficient can be more precisely estimated than the validation-sample-only regression coefficient if the LLM's labels are sufficiently accurate.",
    "10 Intuitively, in this exercise, the LLM's role is something like a missing-value imputer for the existing measurement on the primary sample."
  ]
